# Every change to sources.json or the schema requires review from
# Desk-Modal org owners before merge. This is the gate that keeps the
# curated catalog from being tampered with by anyone who happens to
# get write access to main.
#
# Direct edits to index.json are allowed without review only because
# they're produced by the automated aggregator. Human edits to
# index.json should never happen — if you need to fix the catalog,
# fix sources.json or the aggregator script and let the aggregator
# rewrite it.

# Catalog definition — first line of defence against spam or forged entries
/sources.json           @soarsa

# Trust store + schema — anything that changes what gets signed or how
/schema/                @soarsa

# Aggregator code — changes here can silently redirect downloads or
# bypass signature verification, so review is mandatory
/scripts/               @soarsa

# Workflow files — changes here can fire unauthorized dispatches or
# leak secrets
/.github/workflows/     @soarsa
/.github/actions/       @soarsa
